%BOM---------------------
Date:10/3/2007 11:33:04 AM
From:Jurgis Bekepuris
Anyone has opinion about CSG?

Quicken.com gives its ROE in 25-30% range. If that was the case, it would be a
buy. Unfortunately, using Yahoo numbers to calculate ROE, I get range 12-20%.

It seems a common issue with European (English only?) stocks. They calculate
ROE differently than in US standards. I am not sure exactly how/why, but the
ROEs from websites and annual reports of GSK, AZN, CSG and some others are much
higher than if you use Yahoo numbers for earnings and equity and calculate ROE
yourself.
%EOM----------------------

